20. MEDICAL INFO

If anything goes wrong, people gotta safe you, keep a sheet with things like family phone numbers, blood type, medic conditions, age, diagnosis, doctors number/name/office with you.

19. SLEEP

SLEEP AS GOOD AS YOU CAN PLEASE, It helps your body, digestion, brain, burns cals in the meantime, regulates your appetite. Things like chamomile tea and having a lil something in your stomach before bed helps sleep. Lay in bed at a reasonable time and turn off lights!

18. DONT DO TOO MUCH DR0GS

I know it can be hard, i know its fun and all but please we already have an addiction to our ed behaviors, we are ALL addiction-sensitive. Be mindfull. Especially with dr0gs that kill your appetite. (W33d may help some ppl with restrictive eds, MAY!!!)

17. TAKE YOUR MEDS!!

Please no matter how scary they can be keep taking your meds, and take them as reccomended, if you gotta take em with breakfast eat something, even if its just a couple slices of cucumber and some tea.

16. KEEP SNACKS WITH YOU

idc what you say just do it, especialy when you go outside and ESPECIALLY WHEN UR SPORTING/MOVING. Ive almost FAINTED while on my horse, and almost gotten under a 50KG BAR!! Keep a granola bar with you or fructose tabs idc, dont be stupid like me.

When going outside have atleast 1 person know abt your ed. If anything dangerous happens they can come in and try to keep u alive/explain to ambulance if needed, trust me, you dont wanna go trough near death like me just for not wanting to tell.

14. BE HONEST TO DOCTORS!

I know we lie our asses off to cover up and continue, put please, try to be as gonest as you can, i know we will all keep filling up on water at weigh ins and shit, but be as honest as you can on intake/behaviours/faintings and all, least risk!

13. VITAMINS!

We all balding, forreal we finna be MR. Worldwide by 25. Please look for supplements with: Biotin, Niacin (Vitamin B3) and Vitamin C, and minerals. It will keep your hair as happy as we can keep it.

12. WEAR TIGHT CLOTHING TO BED

Another bloating tip i know, but wearing tight yoga pants or "tummy control shorts" will help you push that gas out and flatten up irregular things. Dont go too tight tho! Leave your upper stomach free and dont do your legs too often. NO BINDERS!!!

11. SNAIL GEL

I know it sounds weird, but as someone who had been bmi 321 maybe even over that loose skin is one of my biggest fears, snail-gel tightens skin, put it on everynight/after showers on legs, stomach, sides and upper arms, it'll moisturize and tighten :)

10. THERMAL CLOTHING

Yesyes, this shit saved my life, it can be teiggering to put on too many layers in the fear we look big. A good quality long sleeve shirt or pants in thermal material will keep you warm without going eskimo, i can assure you its super nice.

9. FIX YOUR POSTURE

Your muscle or organ pains may be partly from your posture too, sitting curled up/crouched down can put pressure on your muscles/organs where it doesnt need to be. I have chronic shoulder pains now, trust me i know it hard to fix a posture, try 5 mins a day!

8. EAT REGULARLY

yes i know shocking to say this to ed people but listen, no matter how low your intake is, this helps. Even at 200 calories a day i found ways to regulate eating times, in the morning, somewhere midday and evening, even if its just a cucumber.

7. YOGA

Yes yes yoga is the hellish word we get from non-ed people that dont understand but hear me out, our muscles are a little weak from not enough nutrients/over excersizing. A couple poses/stretches helps your muscles get ready for the day and helps you get sore less :)

6. WARM BATHS/SHOWERS

I know we all probably take SCORCHING HOT showers anyway cause we are cold as fuck. Heres the thing,it can help releave organ pain and bloating too, make sure to let that water run down your stomach!

5. PROTEIN

I know i know i didnt believe it at first too but protein helps so much, in my first year of when i was deep into my ed i could barely walk without going trough my legs cause my muscles where THAT weak, now i deadlift 75kg. Protein helps you get filled up/energy too!

4. MASSAGE YOUR STOMACH!

Your organs may be a little 🌸under/overworked🌸 which can cause pain but also, especially your lower stomach, it'll help you poop! The more you do it the more you'll get to know your body and you'll know what to do to releave pain/conconstipation :)

3. List of non-bloating foods
